headline: Australia Wireless Router Market Trends Report 2025-2033 | Wi-Fi 6, Smart Home Appliances and Remote Work Drive Demand
summary: The Australia wireless router market is projected to grow from US$ 267.34 million in 2024 to US$ 559.4 million by 2033, at a CAGR of 8.55% from 2025 to 2033. Key growth drivers include increased internet penetration, the rise of smart home devices, remote work trends, and advances in Wi-Fi technology like Wi-Fi 6. headline: T Q2 Deep Dive: Fiber and 5G Expansion Drive Converged Growth, Cost Initiatives Support Margins
summary: Telecommunications conglomerate AT&T (NYSE:T) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales up 3.5% year on year to $30.85 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.54 per share was 1.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
